1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with capacity results and interference alignment techniques, which are core topics in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses interference-limited multi-user channels and cellular interference channels, which are relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Systems and Control) - The paper uses signal-scale alignment, which is a control technique, to achieve capacity results. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions frequency-flat networks, which are relevant to multimedia communication. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses mathematical techniques to derive capacity results and analyze the performance of interference alignment schemes.
